<item>
            <title>[HBASE-10285] All for configurable policies in ChaosMonkey</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-10285</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;For command line runs of ChaosMonkey, we should be able to pass policies. They are currently hard coded to EVERY_MINUTE_RANDOM_ACTION_POLICY. I have made this policy the default, but now if you supply a policy as an option on the command line, it will work.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12687544">HBASE-10285</key>
            <summary>All for configurable policies in ChaosMonkey</summary>
