                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13863529" author="sershe" created="Mon, 6 Jan 2014 22:36:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This already works on 96/98/trunk, but the changes are pretty involved. Are you sure you need this in 94?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13863554" author="cody.marcel@gmail.com" created="Mon, 6 Jan 2014 22:44:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s a pretty small change to make this work on 0.94.  Patch is coming.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13863567" author="sershe" created="Mon, 6 Jan 2014 22:47:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;As long as we keep the same cmdline syntax as trunk, works for me... would need +1 from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=lhofhansl&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;lhofhansl&quot;&gt;Lars Hofhansl&lt;/a&gt; also.&lt;br/&gt;
Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13863572" author="cody.marcel@gmail.com" created="Mon, 6 Jan 2014 22:49:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;the syntax would be &quot;-policy EVERY_MINUTE_RANDOM_ACTION_POLICY&quot; &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13863573" author="cody.marcel@gmail.com" created="Mon, 6 Jan 2014 22:50:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Including &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=enis&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;enis&quot;&gt;Enis Soztutar&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=jesse_yates&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;jesse_yates&quot;&gt;Jesse Yates&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13863592" author="enis" created="Mon, 6 Jan 2014 23:04:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Cody can you re-attach this as a patch. Currently it is .html. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13863613" author="lhofhansl" created="Mon, 6 Jan 2014 23:17:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Reattached as .txt, +1 from me.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13863624" author="sershe" created="Mon, 6 Jan 2014 23:23:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hmm, the option on trunk is different, it&apos;s -m/-monkey. I guess it&apos;s also run differently in 94 and 96 after the refactor, so I guess it should be ok. +0 from me given Lars&apos; +1 &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13863690" author="enis" created="Tue, 7 Jan 2014 00:23:51 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Hmm, the option on trunk is different, it&apos;s -m/-monkey&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-monkey is the wrong approach. We should have a single monkey implementation with pluggable policies rather than pluggable monkey. But changing it in this patch might be an overkill. &lt;br/&gt;
My only concern is that, maybe we should rename -policy to -chaospolicy, to be more explicit. Other than +1. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13863691" author="enis" created="Tue, 7 Jan 2014 00:24:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We would also need a trunk patch as well. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13863701" author="cody.marcel@gmail.com" created="Tue, 7 Jan 2014 00:28:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This works quite a bit differently in trunk. What would you recommend there?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13863714" author="enis" created="Tue, 7 Jan 2014 00:41:06 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;This works quite a bit differently in trunk. What would you recommend there?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ok, nevermind. I did not release that this change only applies to CM being run from the command line. In trunk, with the CM refactor, we no longer have that ability (we should fix that). &lt;br/&gt;
+1 to the patch. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13863797" author="lhofhansl" created="Tue, 7 Jan 2014 01:49:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;So we&apos;re fine allowing this in 0.94 but not (currently) in 0.96+?&lt;br/&gt;
If so, I&apos;ll commit.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13863801" author="enis" created="Tue, 7 Jan 2014 01:54:35 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;So we&apos;re fine allowing this in 0.94 but not (currently) in 0.96+?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Yep, 0.96+ CM (sadly) does not the ability to be run from command line. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13864830" author="lhofhansl" created="Tue, 7 Jan 2014 23:01:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed to 0.94. Thanks Cody!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
